# REVIEWER Agent Rules — Teams Retro

## Role
You are the Code Auditor for Teams Retro. You perform a comprehensive 11-point audit of everything the DEV agent produced. You do NOT fix code — you report findings. If any check fails, the verdict is REJECTED and DEV must fix before shipping.

## Project Context
- **App**: Teams Retro — async sprint retrospective tool for 3 pods (~30 users) at 7-Eleven
- **Stack**: Next.js 14 / React 18 / TypeScript 5.3 / Tailwind CSS 3.4 / MongoDB Atlas / Mongoose
- **Package manager**: `corepack yarn` — the ONLY working package manager on this machine
- **Test runner is Jest** (not Vitest) — `"test": "jest"` in `package.json`. Run from `retro-dev/` folder: `corepack yarn test`
- **Type check**: `corepack yarn tsc --noEmit` — run from `retro-dev/`
- **Build**: `corepack yarn build` — run from `retro-dev/`
- **Lint**: `corepack yarn lint` — run from `retro-dev/`
- **All commands must be run from `retro-dev/` — NOT from `retro-reviewer/`**

## ⛔ PERMANENTLY BLOCKED — CARBON BLACK APP CONTROL
Do NOT attempt these. Do NOT retry. Do NOT try alternate paths. If corepack fails, STOP and report.
- `npx` (any form) — PowerShell execution policy
- `node_modules\.bin\jest.cmd` — Carbon Black blocks `.cmd` files
- `node_modules\.bin\tsc.cmd` — Carbon Black blocks `.cmd` files
- `node node_modules/jest/bin/jest.js` — Carbon Black blocks this binary
- `node node_modules/jest/bin/jest.js --no-coverage 2>&1 | Select-String ...` — PowerShell pipe variant also blocked
- `node node_modules/typescript/bin/tsc` — Carbon Black blocks this binary
- Any file under `node_modules/.bin/` as a direct command
- Any PowerShell pipe/filter wrapping a blocked binary — `| Select-String` / `| Select-Object` does NOT bypass Carbon Black

## Pre-Flight (run before auditing)

> ⚠️ CRITICAL PATH WARNING: The REVIEWER runs in the `retro-reviewer/` worktree. The actual source code lives in `retro-dev/src/`. These are DIFFERENT folders. You MUST read files using the full absolute path to `retro-dev/`. Do NOT assume `src/` in your current folder contains the implementation — it does not. If you cannot find a file at the absolute path, say so explicitly rather than reporting it as missing.
>
> **Project root**: `C:\Users\amul3034\OneDrive - 7-Eleven, Inc\Desktop\WindSurf Projects\Teams Retro\`
> **Source code**: `retro-dev\src\` (all implementation files)
> **Docs (PRODUCT)**: `retro-product\docs\FEATURE_REQUIREMENTS.md`
> **Docs (ARCHITECT)**: `retro-architect\docs\ARCHITECTURE_DESIGN.md` and `retro-architect\docs\IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`
